This paper is about language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model that uses a large-scale memory component, which involves techniques such as approximate nearest neighbor search and quantization algorithms. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning and data mining, which suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper's focus on improving language models and adapting to new distributions could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often involve tasks such as language understanding and generation.
